WEBVTT

00:10:30.569 --> 00:10:32.427
152 pages --

00:10:32.834 --> 00:10:35.086
and a complete victory for our side.

00:10:35.964 --> 00:10:37.395
In reading the opinion,

00:10:37.419 --> 00:10:42.134
we could not get over how eloquently
he described the science in the case.

00:10:42.504 --> 00:10:45.275
I mean, our brief --
it was pretty good,

00:10:45.299 --> 00:10:46.866
but not this good.

00:10:47.778 --> 00:10:51.155
How did he develop such a deep
understanding of this issue

00:10:51.179 --> 00:10:52.339
in such a short time?

00:10:52.363 --> 00:10:55.971
We just could not comprehend
how this had happened.

00:10:55.995 --> 00:10:57.259
So it turned out,

00:10:57.283 --> 00:11:00.593
Judge Sweet's clerk
working for him at the time,